name: Watering Can
description: [TMP] Used to water crops on tilled soil. Watered crops grow <color is="#4ade80">2.5x</color> faster.

name: Bandage
description: Use to quickly regain health. Though rudimentary, this type of bandage was favored by the knights of a lost civilization for the ease with which they could be fashioned from common materials on the battlefield.

name: Barrier Block
description: Invisible Block use to block off areas.

name: Alchemist's Workbench
description: Used to create potions and elixirs. The alchemists of old long sought the secrets to eternal life. Some might say they achieved that grand goal, though perhaps not in the form they imagined.

name: Arcanist's Workbench
description: Used to fashion various arcane implements. The arcane arts are the closest mere mortals have ever come to achieving Avatar powers. Had they mastered them sooner, perhaps they would not have been so easily swayed.

name: Forge
description: The heart of any workshop. Used to forge advanced armor and weapons.

name: Armorer's Workbench
description: Used to craft basic armor.

name: Builder's Workbench
description: Used to create structural building blocks.

name: Campfire
description: Cook basic meals. To many an adventurer, the humble campfire is all it takes to declare a place "home." Unshakeable bonds can be forged while basking in its warmth and all great tales have sparked from its embers.

name: Chef's Stove
description: A built-in kitchen that can be used to make advanced dishes.

name: Farmer's Workbench
description: Used to craft farming accessories and animal feed.

name: Furnace
description: Used to process ore into metal bars. Upgrading reduces smelting times and increases storage capacity.

name: Furniture Workbench
description: Used to craft furniture, storage, and decorative items to personalize your home.

name: Loom
description: Used to process cloth and magical items into materials.

name: The Heart of Orbis
description: A faint disembodied voice can be heard in the presence of this statue. Echoes of a being from beyond the barriers. From the original world.

name: Salvager's Workbench
description: [TMP] Can be used to break down some items into base materials.

name: Tanning Rack
description: Used to process raw hides into leather. Upgrading reduces processing times and increases storage capacity.

name: Trough - Feeding Bench
description: Used to craft farming accessories and animal feed.

name: Blacksmith's Anvil
description: Used to fashion basic weaponry.

name: Workbench
description: A workstation enabling the crafting of more complex tools and items. No artisan is born a creator. Even Avatars need time to hone their craft, particularly when bound by the rules of another's domain.

name: Wooden Bucket
description: [TMP] Can be filled with <color is="#ffffff">Water</color> or used to milk <color is="#ffffff">Cows</color>.

name: Chicken Coop
description: Chickens captured in a <item is="Tool_Capture_Crate"/> can be housed here.

name: Line Brush Tool

name: Mountain Brush

name: Noise Brush Tool

name: Paint Brush Tool

name: Paste Tool
description: Allows you to paste a previously copied or saved block selection

name: Path Brush

name: Prefab Selector Tool

name: Set Anchor Tool

description: Creates Rivers in the ground when you use it

name: Rubble Brush

name: Ruins Brush
description: Allows the user to paint ruins onto the terrain

name: Ruins Brush
description: Generates unique ruined buildings depending on shape and size

name: Ruler Tool
description: Allows you to create line segments between two or more points

name: Scatter Brush Tool
description: Allows you to randomly scatter blocks by specifying a density scale

name: Sculpt Brush Tool

name: Selection Tool

name: Smooth Brush Tool

name: Tint Brush Tool

name: Crude Bedroll
description: When placed, allows an Avatar to set their respawn point to this location.

name: Crude Torch
description: For the last peoples of Orbis, fire was both a source of creativity that elevated their civilization to new heights, and the force that would ultimately lead to their undoing.

name: Statue of The Watcher
description: The whispers were not what compelled the Outlanders to settle in these colder lands. Yet it remains an unquestionable fact that when they arrived, the whispers were already there.

name: Statue of the Founding Builder
description: Long since forgotten by the fallen Scaraks, some few statues of the Founding Builder still stand in their oldest ruins. The few explorers who have since stumbled upon them speak only of an emanating sense of disappointment and disapproval - as if the stone itself was stained by its silent witness of the atrocities committed under the first and last Scarak Empress.

name: Glider
description: Work in Progress

name: Exploration Worldgen Portal
description: Portal that teleports you to Exploration Worldgen, used in the Creative Hub

name: Flat Worldgen Portal
description: Portal that teleports you to Flat Worldgen, used in the Creative Hub

name: Bone Fragments
description: Orbis' most advanced civilizations shared a common trait - the hubris that ultimately led to their downfall. These bone fragments - and the cursed creature from which they were salvaged - should serve as a reminder that some paths are better left untrodden.

name: Sturdy Chitin
description: This resilient material forms the exoskeletons of many creatures found throughout the lands.

name: Cindercloth Scraps
description: When the cursed flame scoured Crucible it left nothing unchanged. Even these scraps of fabric - salvaged from the charred bones of a former denizen - continue to emit an uncanny heat.

name: Linen Scraps
description: Scraps of a common fabric used by many of Orbis' species to fashion their clothing.

name: Shadoweave Scraps
description: This heavy fabric, imbued with a quiet brooding darkness, was devised by the Outlanders prior to their first communion with the Void. Though still a core component of their garb, the secret of its making has long since been lost.

name: Essence of Fire
description: This energy once gave form to the dreams of Crucible's artisans. Today it merely lingers in the creatures that dwell amid the desolated volcanic regions.

name: Essence of Ice
description: When the Outlanders rejected the flame and split from their brethren, they turned instead toward the colder regions and the fragile strength found in the advancing sheets of ice.

name: Essence of Life
description: A form of overflowing life energy found in abundance around plant life on Orbis. In great enough concentrations, perhaps it could even bring forth sentience where it was absent before.

name: Essence of Lightning
description: Raging storms have proved attractive to many creatures over the centuries. Though the true source of such magic is nowhere to be found, the elementals born from its lingering traces still wander the lands.

name: Venom Sac
description: Orbis is home to poisonous creatures of all shapes and sizes. Antidotes distilled from their venom by the Ferans were once prized across the lands.

name: Essence of the Void
description: It's unclear whether creatures of the Void produce this essence, or if its presence is required to sustain their existence. What can be said for certain is that the two are inextricably bound.

name: Voidheart
description: The still-beating heart of a greater denizen of the Void. Not all creatures are born of the Void, yet even those taken and corrupted may bear this same shriveled heart.

name: Essence of Water
description: Even fish have a natural affinity for magic. As water filters through their gills, the concentration grows. Perhaps therein lies the secret to the abyssal creatures lurking in Orbis' darkest depths.

name: Instance Gateway
description: A gateway that allows you to travel to different instances. Interact with it to configure the destination.
